      "content": "A galley kitchen the width of a corridor. Three ingredient bins line the left wall — potato, carrot, onion. The pot sits on the hob. At the far end, a serving hatch opens onto the street.\n\nA man in a high-vis jacket is peering through the hatch. Something warm, he says. Doesn't matter much what.\n\n(Add ingredients to the pot. When the right ones are in, the order completes. Pour the pot to start over. Don't let it burn.)"
