        ["title", "The Hatch"],
        ["state", "order-1"],
        ["noun", "hatch", "window", "serving hatch", "counter"],
        ["transition", "order-1", "order-2", "The man takes his bowl without looking up from his phone. A moment later a small face appears at the hatch. I want the orange one and the purple one, she says. Her mother behind her looks mortified."],
        ["transition", "order-2", "order-3", "The child carries the bowl away two-handed, very carefully. A very large man fills the opening. Everything, he says. All of it."],
        ["transition", "order-3", "order-4", "The large man moves on. A younger man leans in, squinting. My mate Keith was here earlier. He said it was well good. Can I have what he had?"],
        ["transition", "order-4", "order-5", "Keith's mate nods and departs. The hatch darkens. A man in a white coat appears, bearing a clipboard. Environmental Health, he says. I'll be observing your preparation process today."],
        ["transition", "order-5", "done", "The inspector writes something in his notebook. He caps his pen. Adequate, he says. He does not elaborate. He leaves."]
      ],
      "content": "A serving hatch at the far end of the kitchen. The street beyond is audible but not visible."
    },

